<TITLE> Tin Bigha Corridor to be open for polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Lalmonirhat, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com) - The Tin Bigha Corridor will remain open for four days in total over the Jatiya Sangsad and Upazila Parishad election periods. The Corridor is a strip of land on the West BengalBangladesh border for access to Bangladesh's DehgramAngurpota enclave in India. The corridor will remain open a day prior to each election and on both voting days, scheduled for Dec. 29 and Jan. 22 respectively, Col Aftabul Islam, Rangpur BDR sector commander said on Thursday. The decision came from a flag meeting of Bangladesh Rifles and India's Border Security Force on the day. bdnews24.co
